THE member representing Obokun/Oriade Federal Constituency in the House of Representatives, Wole Oke, has claimed that suspected political thugs attacked his supporters in the Government Reserve Area of Osogbo, Osun State. In a statement he personally signed on Friday, February 10, Oke stated that the attack occurred shortly after some northerners living within his constituency visited him and pledged their support for his re-election. READ ALSO: Kogi Election: PDP women leader burnt alive by suspected political thugs Political thugs disrupt collection of PVCs in Osun community Bayelsa/Kogi election: Report raises alarm over arms stockpiling, recruitment of political thugs Edo House Crisis: Police Arraigns 15 Political Thugs According to him, 15 people were inflicted with machete cuts and had to be treated in a hospital in Osogbo. He also alleged that one of the perpetrators was apprehended and handed over to the police for further investigation. Efforts to reach the State Police Command spokesperson, Yemisi Opalola, for comment were unsuccessful. Several calls to her line did not go through, and she did not respond to an SMS.